// Linked codes

<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(nU*) <There's a damn recon plane circling overhead, {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}! Take {#a} {PLANE}s and take off immediately. Don't let him get away, or soon we'll have their whole damn fleet breathing down our necks!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*U*) <We failed to intercept the Japanese reconnaissance flight and a gaggle of enemy aircraft is reported inbound! All we have available is {#a} {PLANE}s. Take off immediately, {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME} and defend our fleet!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*U*) <Enemy reconnaissance managed to report our position, and our destroyer screen reports a large flight inbound! {#a} {PLANE}s on stand-by are available to scramble immediately. {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME} will lead them. Shoot down the attackers! Don't let them get through to our carriers!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*U*) <Our brave fighter jocks managed to let the Japanese recon plane get away, so we are expecting an enemy attack any minute! The only planes available at the moment are {#a} {PLANE}s. {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}, what are you still doing here? Plan to go down with the ship?>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*U*) <The Japanese recon managed to get away from our fighters, and we've just received reports of an incoming enemy bomber force!{#a} {PLANE}s are all that we have ready, we will have to manage with these. {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME} you are ordered to take off immediately!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*U*) <In spite of our best efforts, the Japanese recons have managed to report the location of our task force. We expect an air strike against our forces soon. Only {#a} {PLANE}s are available at the moment. {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}, grab your flight and get your asses to the cockpits!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(nJA) <A deck observer spotted something that appears to be an enemy recon plane in the distance. Your orders are to get another {#a} {PLANE}s and take off immediately, {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*JA) <Enemy reconnaissance gave away our position and bandits will show up soon! We can only scramble {#a} {PLANE}s. {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}, take off immediately and defend the fleet!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*JA) <We failed to intercept the enemy reconnaissance flight and enemy planes are now reported to be inbound. {#a} {PLANE}s are available to take-off immediately. Get on with it, {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*JA) <The American recon flight managed to get away from our interceptors, and we are expecting an enemy attack any minute! The only planes available at the moment are {#a} {PLANE}s. Take off immediately, {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}!>
<ReconIntercept-F-Scramble>(*JA) <Our efforts to catch the American recon planes have failed. We are now sitting ducks for an air strikes, so we are sending {#a} {PLANE}s as a defensive screen. {FULLRANK} {LASTNAME}, you are expeced on the flight deck!>
<Scramble-F-ReconCarrier>(*JA) <{FIRSTNAME}, it is essential we find the whereabouts of the enemy carrier which disturbed us earlier! {LDR_RANK} {LDR_NAME} will lead {#A} {PLANE}s and scout the sector {SECTOR}. >
